name: bootstrap-electron-meteor
description: A template for simplifying the process of creating desktop apps with Electron and Meteor.

scripts.build:osx: node scripts/download --platform=darwin --arch=x64 && node scripts/prepare --platform=darwin --arch=x64 && npm run clean:osx && electron-packager ./app "ElectronMeteor" --out=dist/osx/x64 --platform=darwin --arch=x64 --version=0.27.2 --icon=assets/icons/electronmeteor.icns --ignore="node_modules/(shelljs|colors|adm-zip|tar|gunzip-maybe|rimraf|minimist|fs-extra|electron-packager|electron-builder|electron-prebuilt|electron-rebuild)"
scripts.build:linux: node scripts/download --platform=linux --arch=x64 && node scripts/prepare --platform=linux --arch=x64 && npm run clean:linux && electron-packager ./app "ElectronMeteor" --out=dist/linux/x64 --platform=linux --arch=x64 --version=0.27.2 --icon=assets/icons/electronmeteor.ico --ignore="node_modules/(shelljs|colors|adm-zip|tar|gunzip-maybe|rimraf|minimist|fs-extra|electron-packager|electron-builder|electron-prebuilt|electron-rebuild)"
scripts.osx: npm run build:osx && npm run pack:osx
scripts.win: npm run build:win && npm run pack:win
